other_tests.findings: Deep-vein thrombosis of the left common femoral vein extending into the tibial trunk.
Heterozygosity for the thermolabile C677T polymorphism; protein C, protein S, and antithrombin levels were normal; negative for factor V Leiden and prothrombin gene mutation G20210A.
Occlusive thrombus from the left common femoral vein to the tibial trunk and popliteal vein, with extension of the clot proximally.
Nonocclusive deep-vein thrombosis involving the left femoral, popliteal, and calf veins, with decreased respiratory variability in the left common and external iliac veins.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Indicated progression consistent with recurrent iliofemoral deep-vein thrombosis.

other_tests.findings: Complete occlusion of the iliac veins and an extensive network of collaterals.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Post-procedure showed successful crossing of the occlusion by a guidewire, leading to further intervention.

other_tests.findings: Compression of the left external iliac vein by the crossing internal iliac artery.
